  88→+### `/fly-visual [framework]` — O'Reorg Trail
  89→+
  90→+Launch a retro pixel art game that teaches a web framework's request pipeline. Travel through ~8 stops, answer quiz events disguised as trail decisions, and keep your party alive.
  91→+
  92→+```
  93→+/fly-visual next          # Next.js App Router trail
  94→+/fly-visual rails         # Rails Convention trail
  95→+/fly-visual django        # Django WSGI Wagon trail
  96→+/fly-visual express       # Express Middleware Prairie
  97→+/fly-visual react         # React/Vite Component Canyon
  98→+/fly-visual laravel       # Laravel Artisan trail
  99→+/fly-visual openclaw      # OpenClaw Gateway trail
 100→+/fly-visual               # auto-detect from current repo
 101→+```
 102→+
 103→+**How it works:**
 104→+1. Generates a self-contained HTML game file (no dependencies, no build step)
 105→+2. Opens it in your browser
 106→+3. You travel through the framework's request pipeline as trail stops
 107→+4. Quiz events test your understanding — wrong answers cost health and can kill party members
 108→+5. Arrive at Response Frontier to win, or die of unhandled exceptions trying
 109→+
 110→+**Game features:**
 111→+- Canvas parallax landscape with pixel art wagon
 112→+- Code snippets with syntax highlighting at each stop
 113→+- 5 event types: weather, river crossings, encounters, misfortunes, fortunes
 114→+- Party of 4 members representing key framework concepts
 115→+- Health, supplies, morale, and scoring systems
 116→+- Keyboard controls (1/2/3 for choices, H for hints, Enter to continue)
